annotationA: Putative hydroxypyruvate isomerase; Catalyzes the reversible isomerization between hydroxypyruvate and 2-hydroxy-3-oxopropanoate (also termed tartronate semialdehyde)
annotationB: CG1236; NAD binding; phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: oxidation-reduction process; Belongs to the D-isomer specific 2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase family
